Expense Tracker
A command-line application to manage expenses, demonstrating C++ programming skills including file handling, dynamic memory, and modular design.

Features
Add new expenses with category, amount, and date.
View all expenses in a tabular format.
Delete expenses by their unique ID.
Save and load expense data using file handling.

Open a terminal or command prompt in the project folder and run the following command:
g++ -o expense_tracker main.cpp
This will generate an executable file named expense_tracker.

After compiling, execute the program with:
./expense_tracker   # For Linux/Mac
expense_tracker.exe # For Windows

Use the menu options to add, view, or delete expenses.
Data is automatically saved to expenses.txt.

